“Blood biomarker testing is like looking underneath the hood of a car. 
It makes me a much better competitive athlete. I can't imagine not using InsideTracker. It is vital to creating my health goals. InsideTracker helps me prioritize longevity. I want to be in coaching for a long time and I still want to be a great athlete 20 years down the line. I have really big goals that I want to accomplish. As I get older, I still want to be running and I still want to have plenty of energy for my athletes and my family.”

I’ve made some small manageable changes based on my results!
I’ve added in more soluble fiber like beans and oats to help my cholesterol. 
I’m also focusing more on my recovery and emphasizing sleep. I like to try and have a calm morning hour to myself to drink coffee, organize and stretch before my son wakes up!
Using my @insidetracker app daily has helped keep me accountable 👊🏼

Here she is!! 
Two years of hard work wrapped up into one beautiful package. 

Early copies of Rise & Run have touched down at our homes and we couldn’t be more pleased!!

Less than two months until Rise & Run launches into your hands! 

I know we aren’t supposed to have favorites, but this is my favorite cookbook of ours ☺️.

 For fans who pre-order, we’re giving away a sneak peek of a few of our favorite recipes, including the Everything Bagel 🥯 Superhero Muffin, exclusive discounts from our partners, and Shalane’s at-home strength training routine. We are so excited to share these new recipes with you and can’t wait to hear your thoughts. 

Pre-order now at RunFastEatSlow.com and click on blog to download your free booklet and my workout videos.💪🏼

Do you dream about breakfast 🍳 while you run?!

Meet your new bestie. 
Our next cookbook, Rise & Run, is coming your way this Oct 5th. 
This book will seriously help you revamp your morning routine. 
Out of all three of our cookbooks, this is the book that taught us the most and is the most inspiring book in our lineup.  

Working on Rise & Run meant committing to slowing down and appreciating the simple things in life—taking the time to heal our bodies or linger over freshly baked bread in order to truly absorb our own lessons. We hope to inspire all of you to make a commitment to eliminating “frantic morning syndrome” and prioritize your health and happiness over stress and busyness each and every day.

Thousands of lives have been transformed by our first few books—we know this because you’ve told us! 

Our new book is much more than a collection of breakfast foods for athletes—it’s filled with training advice, marathon tips, and inspiration to start your day better.

Waking right isn’t a fad. It’s a way of life.

Learn more about Rise & Run at runfasteatslow.com. 
While you’re there be sure to subscribe to our newsletter to access sneak-peek recipes, book tour events, and more! 
Rise & Run is available to pre-order anywhere books are sold (save your receipts, pre-order goodies coming soon!).

WOW. 🤩
That was too much fun!!
What an incredible Olympic Games! 

Our team collected some wonderful memories and experiences that we will never forget! 

I’m so proud of our @bowermantc squad. We brought 11 athletes to the Olympic Games and they all gave it everything they had. Which is always enough.

Congrats to our two Olympic Silver medalists 🥈🥈🇺🇸🇨🇦 @courtneyfrerichs @moh_speed23 .
These two serve as role models in running and life. Their performances remind us to keep working on your craft and show up prepared because you never know when it will be your day!

Grateful to work alongside world class humans and world class athletes. 
Arigato ✌🏼Japan!

node.text:
Today our @bowermantc athletes begin competition at the Tokyo Olympic Games!!

I’m taking a moment to feel extra grateful. 🙏🏼

A year ago we were grieving the loss of so much. Dreams derailed and postponed. Our world was upside down.

We are loving the steps along the way; soaking up the ability to travel and savoring connections with friends again.

In the last few weeks we went from the high altitude mountains of park City to sun kissed Hawaii and now to our final destination the Olympic Games in Tokyo!! 

Grateful and excited to be at my 5th Olympic Games is an understatement. ♥️🏟 #bowermantrackclub #bowermanbabes #bowermanbros

With recent travel it’s been hard to keep up our morning routine. So it’s been lovely to fall back into our relaxed habits. Here is what our typical mornings at home look like.

5:00-6am Wake up (no alarm clock because my mommy clock can feel when baby Jack is about to wake)

6am-Drink coffee ☕️ and make Jack’s bottle

6-6:15am snuggle with Jack as he wakes up and drinks his bottle 

6:30-7am PLAY

7am-make breakfast for Jack. 
Our staple is @stonyfield yogurt cups. Jack likes them as is, but I’ve also been adding some fresh summer fruit or cereal for crunchy texture!

Jack has been growing like crazy….(check out his super long hair 🤣) and I’ve noticed his appetite increase as well! Grateful for companies like Stonyfield that value such high quality organic ingredients.

Ohhhhhh and did I say we are traveling again?! We are taking our first family flight today 😳 I appreciate any advice on entertaining a 14month old!🙏🏼✈️

Treat yourself right!

Seriously, how you start your morning has a huge impact on the rest of the day!

I’m a Rise☀️and Run 🏃🏼‍♀️ kind of person so these DIY energy balls save me. 

I can wake up, eat 1-2 of these and be out the door in 30minutes without feeling too full, yet energized throughout my entire run.

Get creative and experiment with different flavors! One of my favorites is adding in some coffee grinds and chocolate chips!

#runfasteatslow #runfastcookfasteatslow #RiseandRun
